1
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:54,033
FORK ON THE LEFT,
NAPKIN ON THE LEFT.

2
00:02:56,266 --> 00:02:57,800
- CHOO-CHOO!
- TRAIN!

3
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:58,766
- CHOO-CHOO!
- TRAIN!

4
00:02:58,766 --> 00:03:00,333
[ laughs ]

5
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:04,966
CARRIE,
WE'RE HAVING DINNER!

6
00:03:04,966 --> 00:03:06,700
OH, SO TIA, WHAT DO YOU THINK
OF YOUR NEW ROOM?

7
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:08,066
ISN'T IT BIG?

8
00:03:08,066 --> 00:03:10,066
- IT'S OKAY.
- WHAT?

9
00:03:10,066 --> 00:03:12,700
SOMETIMES I FEEL
IT'S REALLY COLD,

10
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:13,933
LIKE SOMEBODY'S BLOWING
ON THE BACK OF MY NECK.

11
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:15,900
NO...

12
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:19,233
WELL, YOU DRESSED.

13
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:20,066
WELL, YEAH,
IT'S SUNDAY.

14
00:03:23,733 --> 00:03:25,366
WE'RE JUST A LITTLE MORE CASUAL
AROUND HERE, AREN'T WE.

15
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:31,500
SO, TIA, I DON'T THINK IT'S
ANYTHING BUT A LITTLE DRAFT.

16
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:33,200
WE HAVE TO GET USED TO
THE NEW THINGS AROUND HERE.

17
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:36,000
YOU USED TO DRESS UP
FOR SUNDAYS.

18
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,666
I KNOW,
BUT I DON'T ANYMORE.

19
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:41,833
OKAY, GUYS,
DIG IN, EVERYONE.

20
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:43,100
Woman: THANKS AFTER
THAT DAY OF WORK.

21
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,866
I KNOW,
I'M STARVING.

22
00:03:44,866 --> 00:03:46,100
OKAY, YOU WANT SOME CORN?

23
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,333
Girl: AND SOME BEANS.

24
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:49,733
Woman: SOME BEANS?
OF COURSE YOU CAN.

25
00:03:49,733 --> 00:03:51,166
GOOD GIRL.

26
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:55,700
AREN'T WE GOING TO SAY GRACE
FIRST?

27
00:04:00,433 --> 00:04:03,433
NO, WE DON'T PRAY
AT THE TABLE HERE.

28
00:04:03,433 --> 00:04:04,566
MOM!

29
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:09,466
Woman: THANKS, HONEY.

30
00:04:09,466 --> 00:04:10,800
- SOME GREEN BEANS?
- SURE!

31
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,533
OKAY.

32
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:21,866
BLESS US OUR LORD...

33
00:04:21,866 --> 00:04:25,533
AND THESE OUR GIFTS WHICH
WE ARE ABOUT TO RECEIVE

34
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:28,566
FROM THE BOUNTY
OF CHRIST,

35
00:04:28,566 --> 00:04:32,166
OUR LORD, AMEN.

36
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:33,400
[ clears throat ]

37
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:40,933
UM...

38
00:04:40,933 --> 00:04:42,733
BREAD ROLLS, ANYONE?

39
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:48,366
- CARRIE?
- NO, THANK YOU.

40
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:21,533
UH, HI,
I'M LEW GIBSON,

41
00:05:21,533 --> 00:05:24,566
YOUR NEIGHBOR
FROM A COUPLE OF HOUSES DOWN.

42
00:05:24,566 --> 00:05:27,033
- SAMANTHA LEE,
NICE TO MEET YOU.
- MY PLEASURE.

43
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,366
YEAH, I'VE BEEN WATCHING
YOU ALL DAY.

44
00:05:29,366 --> 00:05:31,533
- YOU HAVE?
- MOVE IN!

45
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:33,833
- OH, OKAY.
- YEAH, ALL DAY.

46
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,000
- LONG DAY.
- I'LL BET.

47
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,700
- YEAH.
- RIGHT?

48
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:40,233
I BROUGHT A LITTLE
HOUSEWARMING GIFT FOR YOU.

49
00:05:40,233 --> 00:05:42,700
- THANK YOU!
- YEAH.

50
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,500
- WOW! THAT'S REALLY NICE.
- WELCOME TO THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

51
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:46,766
THANK YOU,
LOOK, COME ON IN!

52
00:05:46,766 --> 00:05:48,233
OH, NO, YOU'RE PROBABLY TIRED
FROM MOVING ALL DAY.

53
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:50,966
NO, NOT AT ALL.
COME ON!

54
00:05:50,966 --> 00:05:53,733
- UH... YOU SURE?
- YES!

55
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:55,733
IT'S REALLY NICE.

56
00:05:55,733 --> 00:05:57,200
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

57
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,466
- YEAH.
- OKAY.

58
00:06:03,066 --> 00:06:04,500
Woman: SIT DOWN.

59
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,366
THANKS.

60
00:06:08,266 --> 00:06:10,400
YOU KNOW,
WE BOUGHT THE HOUSE AS IS

61
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,666
SO A LOT OF THE PREVIOUS
OWNER'S BELONGINGS

62
00:06:11,666 --> 00:06:12,900
ARE STILL HERE.

63
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,100
- OH...
- YEAH.

64
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,966
- WELL, NICE PIANO.
- THANKS.

65
00:06:16,966 --> 00:06:19,133
YOU PLAY OR YOUR HUSBAND?

66
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:21,566
I DON'T HAVE A HUSBAND.

67
00:06:21,566 --> 00:06:23,333
REALLY?

68
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,633
- [ yells ]
- WHOA!

69
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:28,133
- WHO'S THIS?
- THIS IS TIA.

70
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:31,366
TIA...
HOW OLD ARE YOU, TIA?

71
00:06:31,366 --> 00:06:33,933
- I'M TEN.
- TEN.

72
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:38,033
HMM... THAT MUST MEAN THAT
YOU GO TO LAMB ELEMENTARY.

73
00:06:38,033 --> 00:06:39,400
Tia: YIP-PERDY-DO-DA!

74
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,500
Lew: YIP-PERDY-DO-DA.

75
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:43,033
WELL, I'M THE ART TEACHER
AT LAMB ELEMENTARY.

76
00:06:43,033 --> 00:06:43,800
- Woman: NO WAY!
- YEAH.

77
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,633
OH, WOW!

78
00:06:45,633 --> 00:06:47,566
AS WELL AS THE SIXTH GRADE
COUNSELOR

79
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,966
HELPING THEM TRANSITION
INTO MIDDLE SCHOOL.

80
00:06:49,966 --> 00:06:51,433
- WOW!
- YEAH.

81
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:53,800
HOW YOU LIKE SCHOOL,
TIA?

82
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:56,200
- IT'S OKAY.
- JUST OKAY?

83
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,233
WE'LL HAVE TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT THAT.

84
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:00,566
MAKE IT GREAT!

85
00:07:00,566 --> 00:07:03,633
GO UPSTAIRS
AND PUT YOUR PAJAMAS ON, HONEY.

86
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:05,600
GOOD GIRL.

87
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,900
DON'T FORGET TO SAY HELLO
TOMORROW, TIA.

88
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:08,666
I WON'T.

89
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:11,366
YEAH... JUST AS CUTE
AS HER MOTHER.

90
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,800
[ clears throat ]

91
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,500
YOU'RE GOING TO LIKE IT
HERE IN THIS NEIGHBORHOOD.

92
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:19,566
WE HAVE A LOT OF
SINGLE PARENTS, ACTUALLY.

93
00:07:19,566 --> 00:07:23,633
I'M-- I'M DIVORCED,
ACTUALLY.

94
00:07:23,633 --> 00:07:26,466
AND, UH, WE HAVE ALL KINDS
OF PARENT ACTIVITIES,

95
00:07:26,466 --> 00:07:28,300
PARENTS' NIGHT OUT.

96
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:32,200
WE DO MOVIES, BOWLING,
WINE PAIRING.

97
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,000
Woman: OH, WELL,
SAM ISN'T SINGLE.

98
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,500
HUH?

99
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,566
SHE'S MY WIFE.

100
00:07:35,566 --> 00:07:38,466
OH, HI.

101
00:07:38,466 --> 00:07:41,466
HI, I'M HEATHER.

102
00:07:41,466 --> 00:07:43,566
- HER WIFE.
- MM-HMM.

103
00:07:43,566 --> 00:07:44,566
OH.

104
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:52,400
THAT... OH,
THAT'S INTERESTING.

105
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,333
I-- I'VE NEVER, UH...

106
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:59,066
I'VE NEVER SEEN
A COUPLE OF... WOMENS.

107
00:07:59,066 --> 00:08:00,966
WELL, HERE WE ARE.

108
00:08:00,966 --> 00:08:02,233
- YEAH.
- Sam: YEAH.

109
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:03,800
HERE YOU ARE.

110
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,900
WOW!

111
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:08,100
I MEAN,
IT'S-- IT'S KIND OF LIKE

112
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:10,800
THE EASTER BUNNY OR--
OR UNICORNS.

113
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,666
YOU ALWAYS TALK ABOUT THEM,

114
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:15,966
BUT YOU NEVER REALLY THINK
THEY'RE REAL, YOU KNOW?

115
00:08:15,966 --> 00:08:18,633
SO, UM...

116
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:21,066
HOW LONG HAVE YOU BEEN LIVING
IN THE AREA FOR?

117
00:08:21,066 --> 00:08:22,200
- ME?
- YEAH.

118
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,700
OH, UM...
15 YEARS OR SO.

119
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:28,333
Sam: SO YOU MUST KNOW
THE PREVIOUS OWNER, HUH?

120
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:30,933
Lew: OH, YEAH,
OLD MAN ROBERTS.

121
00:08:30,933 --> 00:08:34,433
SURE, YEAH, I KNEW HIM,
CREEPY OLD GUY.

122
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:37,133
THERE'S KIND OF A SILLY RUMOR
OUT IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD

123
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:39,433
THAT THIS PLACE
IS HAUNTED.

124
00:08:43,866 --> 00:08:46,300
YEAH, THAT'S WHY IT STAYED
ON THE MARKET SO LONG.

125
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,500
- WE DID GET A GOOD DEAL.
- YEAH, WE DID!

126
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,366
YEAH, I BET.
I BET, YEAH.

127
00:08:51,366 --> 00:08:54,200
THE RUMOR IS,
IS THAT UM...

128
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,733
HE WAS THIS CRAZY OLD GUY
WITH A WOODEN DOLL,

129
00:08:57,733 --> 00:09:00,833
AND HE COLLECTED THESE
VICTORIAN DEATH PHOTOS.

130
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,800
CREEPY, RIGHT?
YEAH.

131
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:06,600
AND SO, UH, WHEN HE DIED

132
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:11,300
UM... BECAUSE HIS FAMILY
NEVER CAME TO VISIT HIM,

133
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:13,233
HE'S JUST NEVER LEFT.

134
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:16,266
HE HAUNTS THE PLACE.

135
00:09:16,266 --> 00:09:18,400
OKAY, SO NOW WAIT.

136
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,933
HE DIDN'T ACTUALLY DIE HERE
THOUGH, RIGHT?

137
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,433
HERE? NO.

138
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:23,966
- HE-- HE DIED IN THE HOSPICE.
- Sam: OH, OKAY.

139
00:09:23,966 --> 00:09:25,800
- YEAH.
- Sam: PHEW.

140
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:28,300
Lew: BUT HE HAUNTS
THE PLACE HERE.

141
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,600
Heather: I DON'T KNOW.

142
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,566
YEAH, THERE HE IS.

143
00:09:35,366 --> 00:09:36,700
I SWEAR THAT PAINTING
GIVES ME THE CREEPS.

144
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:38,266
- I HATE IT.
- RIGHT?

145
00:09:38,266 --> 00:09:40,366
- Sam: YEAH.
- I LOVE IT.

146
00:09:40,366 --> 00:09:41,933
I LOVE IT WHEN
SHE'S SCARED.

147
00:09:41,933 --> 00:09:42,766
I GET SO MUCH MORE ACTION.

148
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:49,566
SHE'S SO NAUGHTY.
STOP THAT.

149
00:09:49,566 --> 00:09:53,000
RIGHT... UNICORNS.

150
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,233
[ rumbles ]

151
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:38,333
[ rumbles ]

152
00:10:51,066 --> 00:10:53,466
[ rumbles and creaks ]

153
00:11:02,933 --> 00:11:04,633
[ door creaks ]

154
00:11:12,766 --> 00:11:14,266
[ thud ]

155
00:11:31,066 --> 00:11:32,200
- [ yells out ]
- [ gasps ]

156
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,366
[ sighs ]

157
00:11:34,366 --> 00:11:37,700
TIA, YOU CAN'T BE
IN MY ROOM LIKE THIS.

158
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,600
- COME ON.
- WELL, YOU CAN'T BE
IN MY HOUSE LIKE THIS.

159
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,466
EXCUSE ME?

160
00:11:41,466 --> 00:11:42,266
WELL, IF YOU WANT
TO BE IN MY HOUSE,

161
00:11:42,266 --> 00:11:44,300
YOU CAN PLAY WITH ME.

162
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:46,200
WELL, YOU'LL HAVE TO
TALK TO YOUR MOM ABOUT THAT.

163
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,833
WE COULD JUST HAVE
A TALK, YOU KNOW.

164
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,466
HAVE SOME FUN.

165
00:11:49,466 --> 00:11:51,400
THERE YOU ARE.
COME ON, HONEY,

166
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:54,433
- NO!
- [ knocks on door ]

167
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:55,166
TIA--

168
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:58,500
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO LEARN
TO GET ALONG.

169
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,533
LOOK, I-- I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT THIS SPACE,

170
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:06,400
BUT, UH, WELL,
I DIDN'T REALLY KNOW

171
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:08,266
YOU'RE GONNA BE COMING
TO VISIT AND...

172
00:12:08,266 --> 00:12:09,866
NO, I'M SO HAPPY
ABOUT IT THOUGH.

173
00:12:09,866 --> 00:12:12,266
MOM, MOM-MOM-MOM-

174
00:12:12,266 --> 00:12:13,833
IT'S ONLY GOING TO BE
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS.

175
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,800
I KNOW.
THERE'S JUST NO SPACE.

176
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,800
WELL, I PACK LIGHT.

177
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,700
OH, GOD,
I REMEMBER THAT.

178
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:20,900
LIVING OUT OF
A SUITCASE...

179
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:21,500
YOUR DAD...

180
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:28,833
WE HAD TO TRAVEL THE WORLD
WITH A CARRY-ON BAG.

181
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:32,133
HERE AND THERE,
TRAVELING ALL AROUND.

182
00:12:32,133 --> 00:12:36,166
I'M GLAD THOSE DAYS
ARE OVER.

183
00:12:36,166 --> 00:12:40,166
I-- WHAT
I REALLY MEAN IS...

184
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:43,000
I HOPE YOU GOT MY LETTERS.

185
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,300
YEAH, I DID.

186
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,300
CAN YOU HELP ME WITH THIS?

187
00:12:51,866 --> 00:12:55,200
OH...

188
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,033
I'M THINKING THAT
THE BEST WAY TO KIND

189
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:58,933
OF ORGANIZE OUR LIVES
IS THAT...

190
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:01,366
YOU KNOW, WE ALL KNOW...
WHAT WE'RE ALL GONNA PITCH IN,

191
00:13:01,366 --> 00:13:03,233
HOW WE'RE ALL GONNA PITCH IN.

192
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:07,433
AND UH... I'M WONDERING IF
MAYBE, OH, YEAH.

193
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:10,900
MAYBE... YOU WOULD HELP ME
OUT WITH TIA,

194
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:12,033
TOMORROW ESPECIALLY.

195
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:14,200
WE'VE GOT THIS MEETING.

196
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,000
IT'S INVESTORS
IN SANTA BARBARA--

197
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,833
YES, MOM,
MOM, I WILL.

198
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:19,566
- OH, YOU WILL?
- YEAH.

199
00:13:19,566 --> 00:13:21,566
OH, THANK YOU.

200
00:13:21,566 --> 00:13:24,266
WE'RE JUST GOING TO LEAVE
I THINK ABOUT 5:00,

201
00:13:24,266 --> 00:13:27,266
AND THEN-- WAIT,
YOU TAKE THAT.

202
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:31,233
AND THEN,
WE'LL BE BACK THE NEXT MORNING.

203
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:33,666
I REALLY APPRECIATE IT.

204
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:36,333
OKAY, I THINK
YOU'RE ALL SET UP HERE.

205
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:40,200
[ sighs ] GOOD NIGHT.

206
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,433
IT'S REALLY, REALLY GREAT
TO SEE YOU, CARRIE.

207
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:48,433
MOM...

208
00:13:48,433 --> 00:13:49,366
DO THEY REALLY
NOT BELIEVE IN GOD?

209
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,066
YEAH.

210
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:10,966
[ sighs ] WHY DON'T YOU HAVE
YOUR PJs ON?

211
00:14:10,966 --> 00:14:13,966
I WASN'T IN THE MOOD
FOR PJs.

212
00:14:13,966 --> 00:14:16,100
- WHAT ARE YOU PLAYING WITH?
- WELL, THIS IS BOBBY.

213
00:14:16,100 --> 00:14:18,633
- BOBBY?
- YES.

214
00:14:18,633 --> 00:14:20,566
OKAY, HAND HIM OVER, HONEY,
IT'S GETTING LATE.

215
00:14:20,566 --> 00:14:23,600
- WHY?
- HONEY, HE'S FILTHY.

216
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:26,833
YES, BUT HE'S NOT FILTHY
ON THE INSIDE.

217
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,966
I DON'T CARE WHAT HE IS
ON THE INSIDE, HONEY.

218
00:14:28,966 --> 00:14:29,800
I'M NOT ABOUT
TO ARGUE WITH YOU, OKAY.

219
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:31,566
IT'S TOO LATE.

220
00:14:31,566 --> 00:14:33,566
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
ASLEEP BY NOW.

221
00:14:33,566 --> 00:14:36,533
WELL, WHY WERE YOU MAD
AT DINNER TONIGHT?

222
00:14:36,533 --> 00:14:38,833
I WASN'T MAD AT DINNER.
WHY ARE YOU EVEN SAYING THAT?

223
00:14:38,833 --> 00:14:41,466
WELL, YOU WEREN'T HAPPY.

224
00:14:41,466 --> 00:14:45,400
AND WHO IS THE LORD
AND WHO IS CARRIE TALKING TO?

225
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:49,500
OKAY.
IT'S NOT THAT I WAS MAD.

226
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,800
CARRIE JUST DOES THINGS A LITTLE
DIFFERENTLY TO HOW WE DO,

227
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:55,633
AND I DON'T REALLY LIKE IT.

228
00:14:55,633 --> 00:14:57,066
EVERYTHING ELSE WE CAN TALK
ABOUT TOMORROW.

229
00:14:57,066 --> 00:14:59,633
DEAL?

230
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:03,333
DEAL?

231
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:05,200
- I DON'T THINK WE CAN
TALK ABOUT IT TOMORROW.
- OKAY, HAND OVER THE DOLL.

232
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,333
- NO, WAIT.
